description.narrative: By October 2019, 79% of pregnant women knew their HIV status against the annual target of 90%. Of these, 86% of HIV-infected women were on ARVs. In addition, 25% of HIV-exposed infants received a virologic test for HIV within two months of birth, meeting the annual target of 25%. Of all diagnosed exposed infants, 68% received ARVs for prophylaxis | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:26/12/2019
